<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">What is PDF to Web Converter?</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  LocalGov Drupal includes a <strong>PDF to Web conversion tool</strong> that transforms
  legacy PDF documents into accessible, standards-compliant web pages. This feature uses
  AI to extract text, tables, and structure from PDFs and convert them to semantic HTML.
</p>

<div class="govuk-inset-text">
  <p class="govuk-body govuk-!-margin-bottom-0">
    <strong>Why convert PDFs?</strong> Many councils have important information locked
    in PDF documents that aren't accessible to screen readers, don't work well on mobile,
    and can't be found by search engines. Converting to web content solves all these problems.
  </p>
</div>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-m">Where to find it</h3>

<p class="govuk-body">
  The PDF to Web Converter is available in the Drupal admin menu:
</p>

<ol class="govuk-list govuk-list--number">
  <li>Click <strong>Content</strong> in the admin toolbar</li>
  <li>Select <strong>PDF to Web</strong> from the dropdown</li>
</ol>

<p class="govuk-body">
  Or navigate directly to: <code>/admin/content/pdf-to-web</code>
</p>

